and then plot 1000 random points at the fixed distance of that point
it's not gonna be a circle
square*
and it's not an equivalent of Vector(RandomFloat(-300, 300), RandomFloat(-300, 300), 0) at all
the solution is
Vector(RandomFloat(-1, 1), RandomFloat(-1, 1)):Normalized() * RandomFloat(0, radius)
this is a naive approach because a true random distribution in a circle is a bit more complex
but it will work
